rawContent:
Marvel Mightys - Venomized 8 of 8 üí™üèº

This was quite an easy set to collect. But a rather pricey one...

The Mightys "gamified" - we all heard the speculations. I'd like to point out several things.

Blockchain gaming or video games which utilize blockchain tech have not yet reached real gamers or even begun to have a market share of the gaming industry. They need to be "more" than just P2E which alone is not a guarantee for sustainability (see Axie Infinity). 

Confronted with harsh criticism and biases major players in the gaming industry are still very hesitant if it comes to blockchain (gamers for example hate everything around NFTs with a passion). One other reason is the revenue (why utilizing blockchain tech if they already make money without?). 
 @Ubisoft for example are pursuing their blockchain endeavours with different partners in different directions and they have a partnership with VeVe as we all know. An announcement is imminent and I believe it will be more than simple #DiCo as we're used to.

The gaming industry is reportedly generating more revenue worldwide than the movie industry. One would be foolish to assume VeVe / ECOMI would not at least try to tap in there.

@Avantgarde_NZ will be a first try. But maybe share the knowledge and partner up with #Ubisoft ? Or #Marvel ? 

In case you did not realize it by now: VeVe has a bit more going on with Marvel than just a simple licensing agreement. @Marvel entrusted VeVe with #VeVeComics their whole "future" of digital comics. And such deals are normally not signed with a short term lease. 

The Marvel Mightys are VeVe exclusive. There are and there have been similar cute little Marvel collectibles, but the Mightys have been "invented" for VeVe. With the sole purpose to collect them? I don't think so. 

There "MIGHT" be more to them.

Thx for reading and cheers!

rawContent:
The crazy thing about Ubisoft is they have so many IPs that could dominate their respective genres by being unique, focused experiences that cater to particular niche and playerbase.

For example Ghost Recon could be the best tactical shooter but it ends up being way too casual to try and gain a wider audience.

Rather than trying to appeal to the diehards of each individual genre and absolutely locking it down they try to make every game have mass appeal. It's the exact opposite strategy I'd adopt if I had access to so many different niches and genres.

There are some exceptions like maybe For Honor and Rainbow 6.
